A Tanzanian has been jailed for 15 years for defiling a 17-year-old girl in Homa Bay County.  Zuberi Bado Isa, who appeared before Principal Magistrate Mary Ochieng', had been charged with defilement and being in Kenya illegally.  The court heard that Isa defiled the minor on August 14, 2018, at Miranga village, West Kanyadoto location in Ndhiwa sub-County.  At the time, Isa was working as a farmhand for a resident, Margaret Adhiambo, and found the girl in her house. He reportedly took advantage of his employment to have sex with the teenager on several occasions.  The State called six witnesses. A medical report from Ndhiwa sub-County Hospital revealed that the girl was defiled.   Why court has freed defilement suspect despite DNA proving he impregnated minor  Woman wants man who defiled, killed her daughter, 12, to be given harsher sentence  Man jailed for 25 years over defilement freed after appeal  Eldoret court sets free man jailed 25 years for defiling 10-year-old  President Suluhu will on Tuesday begin a two-day State visit on the invitation of President Kenyatta  Tanzanians set to go to the polls  President Magufuli attracts negative scrutiny for asking Tanzanian farmers to sell produce dearly By Isaiah Gwengi | 2 hours ago By James Omoro | 2 hours ago By James Omoro | 16 hours ago By Julius Chepkwony | 1 day ago